21/09/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Defence Minister Fatmir Mediu met on Tuesday (20 September) with the head of the OSCE Presence in Albania, Ambassador Pavel Vacek.
The two discussed security in the post-election period, armed forces reform and pending tasks related to the country's bid for Euro-Atlantic integration.
Also Tuesday, parliament elected Fatos Beja of the Democratic Party and Ylli Bufi of the Socialist Party as deputy speakers.
Parliament also appointed its eight permanent committees, clearing the way for legislative work to proceed.
(Albanian News - 21/09/05)
